<inglise> COMMISSION DECISION of 28 July 1997 laying down special conditions for the import of bivalve molluscs, echinoderms, tunicates and marine gastropods originating in Thailand (Text with EEA relevance) (97/562/EC) </inglise>
<eesti> KOMISJONI OTSUS 97/562/E&Uuml;, milles s&auml;testatakse Taist p&auml;rit kahepoolmeliste karploomade, okasnahksete, mantelloomade ja meritigude impordi eritingimused 28. juuli 1997 (EMPs kohaldatav tekst) </eesti>
<inglise> THE COMMISSION OF THE EUROPEAN COMMUNITIES, </inglise>
<eesti> EUROOPA &Uuml;HENDUSTE KOMISJON, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the Treaty establishing the European Community, </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse Euroopa &Uuml;henduse asutamislepingut, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to Council Directive 91/492/EEC of 15 July 1991 laying down the health conditions for the production and placing on the market of bivalve molluscs (1), as amended by the Act of Accession of Austria, Finland and Sweden, and in particular Article 9 (3) (b) thereof, </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse n&otilde;ukogu 15. juuli 1991. aasta direktiivi 91/492/EM&Uuml;, milles s&auml;testatakse kahepoolmeliste karploomade tootmise ja turuleviimise tervishoiun&otilde;uded, (1) muudetud Austria, Soome ja Rootsi &uuml;hinemisaktiga, eriti selle artikli 9 l&otilde;ike 3 punkti b, ning arvestades, et: </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas the legislation of Thailand makes the Ministry of Agriculture and Cooperatives, Department of Fisheries (Fish Inspection and Quality Control Division) (FIQCD) responsible for inspecting the health of bivalve molluscs, echinoderms, tunicates and marine gastropods and for monitoring the hygiene and sanitary conditions of production; whereas the same legislation empowers FIQCD to authorize or prohibit the harvesting of bivalve molluscs, echinoderms, tunicates and marine gastropods from certain zones; </inglise>
<eesti> Tai &otilde;igusaktide alusel vastutab kahepoolmeliste karploomade, okasnahksete, mantelloomade ja meritigude tervisliku seisundi kontrollimise ning tootmise h&uuml;gieeni- ja sanitaartingimuste j&auml;relevalve eest p&otilde;llumajandus- ja kooperatiivide ministeeriumi kalandustalitus (kalainspektsiooni- ja kvaliteedikontrolliosakond) (Ministry of Agriculture and Cooperatives, Department of Fisheries - Fish Inspection and Quality Control Division (FIQCD)); samade &otilde;igusaktide alusel antakse FIQCD-le &otilde;igus lubada v&otilde;i keelata teatavates v&ouml;&ouml;ndites kahepoolmeliste karploomade, okasnahksete, mantelloomade ja meritigude p&uuml;&uuml;k; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas the FIQCD and its laboratories are capable of effectively verifying the application of the laws in force in Thailand; </inglise>
<eesti> FIQCD ja selle laboratooriumid on v&otilde;imelised t&otilde;husalt kontrollima Tai kehtivate &otilde;igusaktide kohaldamist; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas the competent authorities of Thailand have undertaken to communicate regularly and quickly to the Commission data on the presence of plankton containing toxins in the harvest zones; </inglise>
<eesti> Tai p&auml;dev asutus on kohustunud edastama komisjonile regulaarselt ja viivitamata andmed toksiine sisaldava planktoni olemasolu kohta kalastusv&ouml;&ouml;ndites; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas the competent authorities of Thailand have provided official assurances regarding compliance with the requirements specified in Chapter V of the Annex to Directive 91/492/EEC and with requirements equivalent to those prescribed in that Directive for the classification of production and relaying zones, approval of dispatch and purification centres and public health control and production monitoring; </inglise>
<eesti> Tai p&auml;dev asutus on andnud ametliku kinnituse direktiivi 91/492/EM&Uuml; lisa V peat&uuml;kis s&auml;testatud n&otilde;uete t&auml;itmise ning k&otilde;nealuses direktiivis s&auml;testatud tootmis- ja &uuml;lekandmispiirkondade liigitamist, v&auml;ljastus- ja puhastuskeskuste heakskiitmist ning rahva tervise kontrollimist ja tootmisj&auml;relevalvet k&auml;sitlevate n&otilde;uetega samav&auml;&auml;rsete n&otilde;uete t&auml;itmise kohta; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas Thailand is eligible for inclusion in the list of third countries fulfilling the conditions of equivalence referred to in Article 9 (3) (a) of Directive 91/492/EEC; </inglise>
<eesti> Tai sobib kandmiseks direktiivi 91/492/EM&Uuml; artikli 9 l&otilde;ike 3 punktis a osutatud vastavustingimusi t&auml;itvate kolmandate riikide loetellu; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas Thailand wishes to export to the Community frozen or processed bivalve molluscs, echinoderms, tunicates and marine gastropods which have been sterilized or heat-treated in accordance with the requirements of Commission Decision 93/25/EEC (2), amended by Decision 97/275/EC (3); </inglise>
<eesti> Tai soovib eksportida &uuml;hendusse selliseid k&uuml;lmutatud v&otilde;i t&ouml;&ouml;deldud kahepoolmelisi karploomi, okasnahkseid, mantelloomi ja meritigusid, mida on steriliseeritud v&otilde;i kuumt&ouml;&ouml;deldud vastavalt komisjoni otsuse 93/25/EM&Uuml; (2) (muudetud otsusega 97/275/E&Uuml; (3)) n&otilde;uetele; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas, for this purpose, the production areas from which bivalve molluscs, echinoderms, tunicates and marine gastropods may be harvested and exported to the Community should be designated; </inglise>
<eesti> selleks tuleks m&auml;&auml;ratleda tootmispiirkonnad, kust kahepoolmelisi karploomi, okasnahkseid, mantelloomi ja meritigusid v&otilde;ib p&uuml;&uuml;da ja &uuml;hendusse eksportida; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas the special import conditions should apply without prejudice to decisions taken pursuant to Council Directive 91/67/EEC of 28 January 1991 concerning the animal health conditions governing the placing on the market of aquaculture animals and products (4), as last amended by Directive 95/22/EC (5); </inglise>
<eesti> impordi eritingimusi kohaldatakse, ilma et see piiraks n&otilde;ukogu 28. jaanuari 1991. aasta direktiivi 91/67/EM&Uuml; (akvakultuuriloomade ja -toodete turuleviimist reguleerivate loomatervishoiun&otilde;uete kohta, (4) viimati muudetud direktiiviga 95/22/E&Uuml; (5)) kohaselt tehtud otsuste kohaldamist; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas the measures provided for in this Decision are in accordance with the opinion of the Standing Veterinary Committee, </inglise>
<eesti> k&auml;esoleva otsusega etten&auml;htud meetmed on koosk&otilde;las alalise veterinaarkomitee arvamusega, </eesti>
<inglise> HAS ADOPTED THIS DECISION: </inglise>
<eesti> ON VASTU V&Otilde;TNUD K&Auml;ESOLEVA OTSUSE. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 1 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 1 </eesti>
<inglise> The Ministry of Agriculture and Cooperatives, Department of Fisheries - Fish Inspection and Quality Control Division - (FIQCD) shall be the competent authority in Thailand for verifying and certifying that bivalve molluscs, echinoderms, tunicates and marine gastropods fulfil the requirements of Directive 91/492/EEC. </inglise>
<eesti> P&otilde;llumajandus- ja kooperatiivide ministeeriumi kalandustalitus (kalainspektsiooni- ja kvaliteedikontrolliosakond) (Ministry of Agriculture and Cooperatives, Department of Fisheries - Fish Inspection and Quality Control Division - (FIQCD)) on Tai p&auml;dev asutus, mis kontrollib ja t&otilde;endab kahepoolmeliste karploomade, okasnahksete, mantelloomade ja meritigude vastavust direktiivi 91/492/EM&Uuml; n&otilde;uetele. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 2 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 2 </eesti>
<inglise> Bivalve molluscs, echinoderms, tunicates and marine gastropods originating in Thailand and intended for human consumption must originate in the authorized production areas listed in the Annex hereto. </inglise>
<eesti> Taist p&auml;rit ja inimtoiduks etten&auml;htud kahepoolmelised karploomad, okasnahksed, mantelloomad ja meriteod peavad olema p&auml;rit k&auml;esoleva otsuse lisas loetletud tootmispiirkondadest. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 3 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 3 </eesti>
<inglise> This Decision is addressed to the Member States. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esolev otsus on adresseeritud liikmesriikidele. </eesti>
<inglise> Done at Brussels, 28 July 1997. </inglise>
<eesti> Br&uuml;ssel, 28. juuli 1997 </eesti>
